**`TabController.mm`: lambda return type deduction fails due to `bool`/`BOOL` mismatch**

In `UI/AppKit/Interface/TabController.mm`, `windowShouldClose:` defines a lambda without an explicit return type (~line 1498):

```cpp
auto confirm_canceling_downloads = [&]() {
    if ([delegate tabCount] > 1)
        return true;
    return [(Application*)NSApp confirmCancelActiveDownloads];
};
```

`true` deduces `bool`, but `confirmCancelActiveDownloads` returns `BOOL` (`signed char` on Apple platforms). C++ lambda return-type deduction requires all return statements to produce identical types, resulting in a `-Wreturn-type` warning with Clang.

Fix — add explicit return type:

```cpp
auto confirm_canceling_downloads = [&]() -> bool {
```

`BOOL` values `YES`/`NO` convert to `bool` correctly; no semantic change.
